
= Hydroponics is the practice of growing plants in nutrient-enriched water rather than soil. Aquaponics is a kind of hydroponics that uses the water from fish tanks. This eliminates the need for an input of nutrients. 

=More Information=

* see http://opensourceecology.org/wiki/hydroponics at [[Open Source Ecology]]

